.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "February 2026" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic command line interpreter that executes commands read from standard input.
It behaves similarly to
.BR sh (1)
in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

In interactive mode, the shell displays a prompt and waits for user input.
In non-interactive mode, the shell reads commands from standard input (for example, via a pipe).

The shell executes programs by searching for them in the directories listed in the
.B PATH
environment variable, unless the command contains a slash character ('/'),
in which case it is treated as a path.

.SH INVOCATION
Run the shell in interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
.B ./hsh
.RE
.PP
Run the shell in non-interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
.B echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.RE

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment.
.TP
.B cd
Changes the current working directory.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns
.B 0
on normal exit.
If a command is not found, the shell prints an error message to standard error and returns status
.BR 127 .

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
A colon-separated list of directories used to search for commands.

.SH EXAMPLES
Execute a command using PATH search:
.PP
.RS
.B ls -l
.RE
.PP
Execute a command by full path:
.PP
.RS
.B /bin/ls
.RE

